From 5dd3392382b613764f06b065910aaf74bff6bbeb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mainframe98 <k.s.werf@hotmail.com>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2026 19:46:13 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 46/50] Correct symbol information for moved functions

Summary:
Functions moved between extensions are reported multiple times, once for each extension.
Sometimes they include which version of PHP was the last version that provided that function for that extension.
The next entry then reports a newer version of PHP as the first version that supported that function for the other extension.

This information is not relevant for our use cases, so we only record the first PHP version the function appeared in and (if applicable) the last.

Closes T16546

Test Plan: Looked at the diff for symbol-information.json.

Reviewers: O1 Blessed Committers, aklapper

Reviewed By: O1 Blessed Committers, aklapper

Subscribers: aklapper, tobiaswiese, valerio.bozzolan, Matthew, Cigaryno

Maniphest Tasks: T16546

Differential Revision: https://we.phorge.it/D26831
